data.content:
`Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi 10.0` pulls in `Microsoft.OpenApi` v2.x, which has several breaking changes affecting your code. Here's each issue and its fix:

---

**1. Namespaces removed** тАФ `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models` and `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` no longer exist:
```csharp
// Before
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

// After
using Microsoft.OpenApi;
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
```

**2. `OpenApiString` removed** тАФ Use `JsonNode`:
```csharp
// Before
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After
param.Schema.Example = JsonNode.Parse("\"1.0\"");
```

**3. `OpenApiSecurityScheme.Reference` replaced** тАФ Use `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference` directly:
```csharp
// Before
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};

// After
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2", null);
```

**4. Collections may be null** тАФ `operation.Parameters`, `operation.Responses`, etc. can now be null:
```csharp
operation.Responses ??= new OpenApiResponses();
operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

var param = operation.Parameters?.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
```

**5. `OpenApiSchema.Nullable` removed** тАФ OpenAPI 3.1 uses JSON Schema's `type: ["string", "null"]` instead of `nullable: true`. Your schema transformer that sets `.Nullable = false` should be removed entirely тАФ it has no equivalent in v2.

---

### Full corrected code:

```csharp
using Microsoft.OpenApi;
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters?.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonNode.Parse("\"1.0\"");
    }

    operation.Responses ??= new OpenApiResponses();
    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2", null);
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes.ToList() }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

// The Nullable property no longer exists тАФ remove this transformer
// unless you need other schema modifications.
```
